  "response": "The Vice President of India is the ex-officio Chairman of the Rajya Sabha, which is the upper house of the Parliament of India. As of my last update, the Vice President and thus the Chairman of the Rajya Sabha is Jagdeep Dhankhar. The Rajya Sabha does not have a \"Speaker\" like the Lok Sabha; instead, it has a Chairman and a Deputy Chairman. The Deputy Chairman of the Rajya Sabha is elected from amongst its members.",
